		<div class="post" id="post-2755633">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2755633)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2755633">
																		Eastern Samothrace
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163616" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;" >MrWrong</a></span> <span class="odate time_1488089325 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">26 Feb 2017 06:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2755633">
									

<p>Although I effectively changed the crosslink to 1173 wholesale, I will admit that I find the take here to be interesting.</p>
<p>However, I am more concerned with the implication of diminishing 1173's story. I mean, 1173's story has even the O5 unsure of the truth. Since this 001 proposal and log are presented as knowledge privy to the O5, many crosslinks to SCP-1173 risk that diminishment. I myself fell into that trap before I removed the reference (I wrote that Samothrace happened in the previous reality, which was rectonned away).</p>
<p>It is my fault for not accounting for that, but this gave me impetus to do something. Keeping the truth within O5-1 should retain the mystery (the only O5 not involved in 1173's article).</p>
<p>Nonetheless, I do think the story presented here can be given more life than a few sentences (i.e. a full article).</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Phenomenon:</strong> The Islamic Republic of Eastern Skanta</p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> A political body formed from the refugees from the ruins of Skanta, a small town near London, arrived to a new land to escape the war called the Islamic Republic of Eastern Skanta. The Republic was well known for its memetic anomalies, which they would use to assist Her Majesty's Foundation for the Secure Containment of the Paranormal.</p>
<p><strong>Analogue in Current Reality:</strong> According to SCP-████, the Islamic Republic of Eastern Skanta contracted an anti-memetic virus, which began to destroy the concept of the Republic itself. It is said that the Council that governed the Republic enacted an emergency protocol to <a href="/scp-1173">change the republic's name</a> from every single recorded item referencing them, thus making them immune from further metaphysical manipulation. However, due to the outbreak, The new Republic now only exists partially within the current reality.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>P.S. IIRC, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/oria-025-117">ORIA does believe that Eastern Samothrace is partially in reality.</a></p>

							</div>

								
